Command> echo $SSH_CONNECTION

TL;DR> Identifies the client and server ends of the connection.

Keywords> ssh
        > ip


Description>
           >  The variable contains four space-separated values:
           >        1. client IP address
           >        2. client port number
           >        3. server IP address
           >        4. server port number.
           >
           > e.g.
           >    192.168.7.21 57868 192.168.6.4 22
           >    ------------ ----- ----------- --
           >         1         2        3       4
           >

Reference> https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/120080/what-are-ssh-tty-and-ssh-connection
